{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778985364772,"sessionID":"ses_1cc45ced6ffetlmObhyMpk3zqs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YNNSPZt2TTIjOapnoUmp0EA5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Implemented the requested cleanup for Entner-Doudoroff pathway terms.\n+\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0009255`, `GO:0061679`, `GO:0061680`, and `GO:0061681` with `replaced_by: GO:0061678`.\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0061688` with `replaced_by: GO:0006096`.\n+- Updated `GO:0061678` to remove the MetaCyc grouping-class xref and retain the variant pathway IDs as `skos:narrowMatch` xrefs, including `MetaCyc:ENTNER-DOUDOROFF-PWY`.\n+- `make travis_build` passes after the edits.\n+\n+Annotation impact noted during review:\n+\n+- `GO:0009255` has existing direct annotations, so those should migrate to `GO:0061678` via the replacement.\n+- `GO:0061688` has 10 direct CGD IEA annotations, which should migrate to `GO:0006096` via the replacement.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Summary:\n+\n+This change resolves issue `#31916` by collapsing the Entner-Doudoroff pathway variant terms into the broader retained parent term and obsoleting the separate glycolytic-process-via-ED term as requested in the issue thread.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0009255` Entner-Doudoroff pathway through 6-phosphogluconate\n+  - `replaced_by: GO:0061678`\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0061679` Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate\n+  - `replaced_by: GO:0061678`\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0061680` Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde\n+  - `replaced_by: GO:0061678`\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0061681` Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate\n+  - `replaced_by: GO:0061678`\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0061688` glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway\n+  - `replaced_by: GO:0006096`\n+\n+For each obsolete term, I removed logical axioms and other term content that should not remain on an obsolete class, preserved the historical definition provenance, added a `term_tracker_item` back to issue `#31916`, and added a short obsoletion comment.\n+\n+I also updated the surviving parent term `GO:0061678`:\n+\n+- removed `xref: MetaCyc:Entner-Doudoroff-Pathways` because it is a MetaCyc grouping class\n+- added the requested variant pathway mappings as narrow matches:\n+  - `MetaCyc:PWY-8004`\n+  - `MetaCyc:NPGLUCAT-PWY`\n+  - `MetaCyc:PWY-2221`\n+  - `MetaCyc:ENTNER-DOUDOROFF-PWY`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue discussion explicitly requested obsoletion of the pathway-variant GO terms in favor of the broader parent `GO:0061678`, consistent with treating these MetaCyc entries as pathway variants better represented outside the GO class hierarchy.\n+- The issue discussion also explicitly requested obsoletion of `GO:0061688` to its broader parent `GO:0006096`.\n+- Retaining the MetaCyc variant identifiers on `GO:0061678` as `skos:narrowMatch` preserves the external mapping signal without keeping separate GO classes for each variant.\n+\n+Annotation impact reviewed:\n+\n+- `GO:0009255` has direct annotations in AmiGO, including experimental annotations and automated annotations; these should move to `GO:0061678` via `replaced_by`.\n+- `GO:0061679`, `GO:0061680`, and `GO:0061681` appeared to have no direct annotations in the annotation lookup used here.\n+- `GO:0061688` has 10 direct CGD IEA annotations, matching the issue discussion; these should move to `GO:0006096` via `replaced_by`.\n+\n+Validation:\n+\n+- Pre-validation: `make travis_build` passed before editing.\n+- Post-edit validation: `make travis_build` passed after editing.\n+\n+Checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed and request was clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: not needed beyond issue discussion and annotation impact review\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: relevant GO terms inspected in `go-edit.obo`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: checked; no new logical definitions added\n+- [x] EDITS: used checkout/edit/checkin workflow via `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: removed obsolete-term logical axioms and retained only appropriate replacement metadata\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: used term obsoletion workflow\n+- [x] METADATA: obsolete stanzas have correct name/def/comment/tracker/replacement structure\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: no new PMIDs introduced\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: local commit created for `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@\n+Implemented the requested cleanup for Entner-Doudoroff pathway terms.\n+\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0009255`, `GO:0061679`, `GO:0061680`, and `GO:0061681` with `replaced_by: GO:0061678`.\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0061688` with `replaced_by: GO:0006096`.\n+- Updated `GO:0061678` to remove the MetaCyc grouping-class xref and retain the variant pathway IDs as `skos:narrowMatch` xrefs, including `MetaCyc:ENTNER-DOUDOROFF-PWY`.\n+- `make travis_build` passes after the edits.\n+\n+Annotation impact noted during review:\n+\n+- `GO:0009255` has existing direct annotations, so those should migrate to `GO:0061678` via the replacement.\n+- `GO:0061688` has 10 direct CGD IEA annotations, which should migrate to `GO:0006096` via the replacement.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n=====================================================