Cyc variant identifiers on `GO:0061678` as `skos:narrowMatch` preserves the external mapping signal without keeping separate GO classes for each variant.\n+\n+Annotation impact reviewed:\n+\n+- `GO:0009255` has direct annotations in AmiGO, including experimental annotations and automated annotations; these should move to `GO:0061678` via `replaced_by`.\n+- `GO:0061679`, `GO:0061680`, and `GO:0061681` appeared to have no direct annotations in the annotation lookup used here.\n+- `GO:0061688` has 10 direct CGD IEA annotations, matching the issue discussion; these should move to `GO:0006096` via `replaced_by`.\n+\n+Validation:\n+\n+- Pre-validation: `make travis_build` passed before editing.\n+- Post-edit validation: `make travis_build` passed after editing.\n+\n+Checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed and request was clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: not needed beyond issue discussion and annotation impact review\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: relevant GO terms inspected in `go-edit.obo`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: checked; no new logical definitions added\n+- [x] EDITS: used checkout/edit/checkin workflow via `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: removed obsolete-term logical axioms and retained only appropriate replacement metadata\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: used term obsoletion workflow\n+- [x] METADATA: obsolete stanzas have correct name/def/comment/tracker/replacement structure\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: no new PMIDs introduced\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: local commit created for `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go